author: The Current
description:
Watch a three-song set by Of Monsters and Men recorded live at The Current
Support The Current: https://support.mpr.org/youtube or hit the Thanks button

Icelandic band Of Monsters and Men have been together for 15 years, but they took a bit of time off before recording their latest album, "All Is Love and Pain in the Mouse Parade." When the band reunited in the studio to work on the album, they rediscovered the joy of playing together.

When Of Monsters and Men visited St. Paul in November, they played two back-to-back nights at the Palace Theatre. Between those shows, Of Monsters and Men visited The Current studio to play songs from the new album. Watch and listen to the music performances above.

Songs Performed
00:00:00 The Towering Skyscraper at the End of the Road
00:04:44 Fruit Bat
00:11:36 The End
All songs from Of Monsters and Men’s 2025 album, All Is Love and Pain in the Mouse Parade, available on Skarkali Records/Virgin Music Group.

Musicians
Nanna Bryndis Hilmarsdottir -
title: Of Monsters and Men perform songs from 'All Is Love and Pain in the Mouse Parade" at The Current

Of Monsters and Men 2025 interview recorded live at The Current
Support The Current: https://support.mpr.org/youtube or hit the Thanks button

Icelandic band Of Monsters and Men have been together for 15 years, but they took a bit of time off before recording their latest album, "All Is Love and Pain in the Mouse Parade." When the band reunited in the studio to work on the album, they rediscovered the joy of playing together.

When Of Monsters and Men visited St. Paul in November, they played two back-to-back nights at the Palace Theatre. Between those shows, Of Monsters and Men visited The Current studio to play songs from the new album and then sat down with host Gannon for a conversation about the new album and about playing live. Watch the conversation above.

Of Monsters and Men’s 2025 album, All Is Love and Pain in the Mouse Parade, is available on Skarkali Records/Virgin Music Group.

description:
Watch Mt. Joy's performance of "Astrovan" in studio
Support The Current: https://support.mpr.org/youtube or hit the Thanks button

Spanning the summer of 2025, Los Angeles-based band Mt. Joy have experienced what singer/guitarist Matt Quinn describes as “the best tour we've ever had.” When their tour took them to the Twin Cities, Mt. Joy visited The Current studio to play songs from a couple of their albums. Watch and listen to a performance of "Astrovan" above.
